 inception, and although I have played mainly on SZ lately, my greatest loyalty is always to TZ since it was the home of my first real character.  Recently, I decided to start playing more on TZ, and I have noticed some disturbing things not only on TZ as a whole, but within AA as well.<br><br>The two greatest challenges facing all of us right now seem to be 1) where did the hell did all the x-teamers come from?  When I stopped playing TZ regularly the only x-teamers were Pande, and everyone looked at them with disgust.  And 2) Why is there no &quot;real&quot; light unity on the server.<br><br>It is because of both of these things that I am addressing you today.  What I would like to propose is that we make a concerted effort to group together more, and try to bring the light guilds into unison.  I am going to be making this same effort with as many honorable light guilds as possible, in order to form a loose coalition for a common purpose...defend our lands, and help us to all grow in stature.  Right now I think we do an adequate job when grouping but I believe we can so much more…I envision light only chat channels, web pages and completely controlled zones.<br><br>One thing I am keenly away of also, is that we do not lose our unique identities as we do this.  I am not suggesting that we all merge to form one large guild, but rather that we all work together as common allies.<br><br>I look forward to hearing from you in game, and I invite you to post on our website so that we can learn about your guild and your values and traditions.  In game, I will probably be playing either Koolcat or Zayis, and I look forward to hearing from you.<br><br>Take care,<br>Koolcat <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub77.ezboard.com/umcshortie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>McShortie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FFFF00