 does not matter to me what they do after, I loot and scoot.  So what do I care what they think about defeating a light.  Getting ganked is just part of the game.<br>I have seen the ruleset for SZ, I was not sure I could deal with the rules after being on Tallon for so long.  You do have a point though.  I will however, still not go 4 team, and neither will Archaic Arbitrators, while I am leading it.<br>I do not think to be honest that lighties are superior just right.  I could care less what the &quot;newbs&quot; think.  We can still get our epics and have fun playing this game.  Some said that once the sever started going 4 team that the light guilds would fold, there are several that have not and I do not believe they will.<br>remember to have fun and just don't be lame and we can continue to play. <p>"Character is what you are in the dark" and when no one is looking!<BR>Archaic Arbitrator's Leader with an eye on Justice and the Family of Archaic Arbitrators.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub77.ezboard.com/uteeowe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>teeowe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/9/02 7:22:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub77.ezboard.com/ftallonzektimes4735guildsoftallonzek.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=562.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ALL LIGHT GUILDS READ!!!</span><hr size=1> Toldek, et.al.-<br><br>/ooc-<br>I couldn't agree more.  I like the good v. evil character of Tallon; I choose TZ over Vallon because I read VZ was more team v team, while TZ was more dark v. light.<br><br>I readily recognize that dark v. light is imperfect when it comes to dividing up teams, since many lights are evil and many darks play good or at least choose agnosticism.<br><br>The environment is set up as good versus evil too.  This makes it seemingly inconsistent to play PvP against, say,  elves in Norrath when dwarves have an alliance against them.  If shorts are at war with elves and humans why can I trade in their cities with little no faction adjustment work?  This is the main problem with TZ as it exists today.<br><br>When I was a DM in D&amp;D as a much younger man, I disallowed evil player characters.  I believe then as now that fantasy role-playing ought to be heroic.  Worshipping Bertox or Inny is far from heroic.<br><br>I play a Dwarf Paladin as my main.  I avoid grouping with SKs and necros.  I protested loudly when my former guild, lron Legion, invited a human Shadow Knight.  When the guild leadership changed hands, and other policy changes that I disagreed with were made, I left to start a new guild.  &lt;i&gt;New Justiciars&lt;/i&gt; is new and small, but rewarding.  We DO NOT allow evil characters, so no worshippers of Bertox, Inny, Cazic or Rallos.  No SKs or necros are allowed of course, since they must be evil.  We are even discussing allowing agnostic darks, but have yet to do so for fear of being accused of being 4-teamers.  Others have asked me how can we do plane raids if we have no necros?  To be honest I haven't given this much thought, but I expect we'll make it ok; it will make raids more challenging, but possibly more fun for it.<br><br>Why don't I play on Sullon?  Because its more than good v. evil.  There is also a neutral team and the dynamics don't make for good roleplay.<br><br>Summarizing, TZ's racial PvP is out of alignment with PvE.  Good v. Evil is what I am trying to roleplay, and TZ seemed the best, yet imperfect, choice.  Sullon's rules and neutral team make it a less perfect choice for me.<br><br>Lighties, or more precisely, non-evil characters unite!<br><br>Hunt safely! Hunt well!<br><br>Theodus (surnameless)<br>Guildleader and co-founder of New Justiciars<br>Paladin of Brell Serilis<br>42 Crusades (and counting)<br><br>PS. Send me a tell in game and I'll be happy to discuss New Justiciars in more detail. - Theo <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub77.ezboard.com/uteeowe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>teeowe</A> at: 4/9/02 7:25:03 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub77.ezboard.com/ulunanare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lunanare</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazonians Slave Keeper</span><br>  Posts: 397<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/9/02 11:05:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub77.ezboard.com/ftallonzektimes4735guildsoftallonzek.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=562.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://ew2.lysator.liu.se/loth/c/l/claire/syrela.jpg height=200 width=145></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ALL LIGHT GUILDS READ!!!</span><hr size=1> that light alliance became the underdogs. This doesn't mean we will fold and succomb to what everyone else is doing. It simply means we will think of new tactics to go about things... this is a new idea. Why bash it before it even begins. If you don't want to be involved with it then don't. The lights have 3 teamed since the begining of the server, so why complain about it now? <p>"Do not ask which creature screams in the night, Do not question who waits for you in the shadow. It is my cry that wakes you in the night, And my body that crouches in the shadow. I am Lunanare and you are the puppet That dances to my tune." </p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub77.ezboard.com/ftallonzektimes4735guildsoftallonzek.showPrevMessage?topicID=562.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub77.ezboard.com/ftallonzektimes4735guildsoftallonzek.showNextMessage?topicID=562.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><b